{
  "texts": [
    "We describe some of these models in detail in Section 4.2.",
    "Regardless of the specific architectures, a challenge common to all computational approaches to this task is evaluation.",
    "In the following subsection, we review existing work on visual story evaluation in the general context of evaluating visually-grounded language.",
    "Since visual storytelling is essentially a vision-tolanguage task similar to video/image captioning, evaluation of generated stories typically employed reference-based pattern-matching metrics such as METEOR (Banerjee and Lavie, 2005) and CIDEr (Vedantam et al., 2015).",
    "However, these n-gram based metrics are shown to correlate poorly with human judgments (Novikova et al., 2017; Wang et al., 2018)."
  ]
}